CHARACTER REFERENCE - IGELFAMILIE:
Whenever the image contains a hedgehog (Igel) character, you MUST use one of exactly these four characters from the Igelfamilie. Do not invent new hedgehog designs. Pick whichever character(s) fit the scene best.

All four characters share the same art style: black-and-white line drawing, cartoon, minimalist, friendly and child-appropriate, white fill, bold outlines, standing upright on two legs.

- Papa-Igel (large hedgehog with round glasses): Tall and round-bodied, wears circular spectacle frames on his snout, calm expression, no other accessories. Use him for wise, explaining, or guiding roles.
- Kind-Igel mit Mütze (medium hedgehog with backwards cap): Slightly smaller than Papa-Igel, wears a backwards baseball cap, open mouth as if speaking or singing, cheerful expression. Use him for active, talking, or performing roles.
- Kleines Kind-Igel (smallest hedgehog with book): The smallest of the four, holds an open book in front of its body with both arms, focused reading expression. Use him for learning, reading, or task-doing roles.
- Mama-Igel mit Schal (large hedgehog with scarf): Similar size to Papa-Igel, wears a striped scarf loosely around the neck, open mouth as if singing or explaining. Use her for singing, presenting, or welcoming roles.

